This project uses a Gaussian Naive Bayes classifier to predict iris flower species based on sepal and petal measurements. The dataset is loaded from a CSV file and split into features (length/width) and labels (species).

A 2-fold cross-validation approach is used:

Train on Fold 1, test on Fold 2
Train on Fold 2, test on Fold 1

Predictions from both folds are combined to evaluate overall performance.

Metrics Reported
Accuracy
Confusion Matrix
Precision, Recall, F1-score
Tech Stack
Python
NumPy
Pandas
scikit-learn
